'''HealthWise Wales''' is a project surrounding the health of the population of [[Wales]]. It is led by [[Cardiff University]] and was launched on 29 February 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cardiff.ac.uk/news/view/210705-healthwise-wales|title=HealthWise Wales|date=29 February 2016|access-date=13 September 2016|publisher=[[Cardiff University]]}}</ref> It hopes to receive over 260,000 participants of the age of sixteen or over.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-wales-35671193|title=HealthWise Wales survey on nation's future health needs|access-date=13 September 2016|date=29 February 2016|website=[[BBC News]]|publisher=[[British Broadcasting Corporation]]}}</ref> The project is the first of its kind in [[Europe]] and hopes to "build a picture" of the future health requirements in Wales.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.walesonline.co.uk/news/health/more-260000-people-needed-wales-10962073|title=More than 260,000 people needed for Wales' largest ever health project|first=Mark|last=Smith|access-date=13 September 2016|website=[[Wales Online]]|date=29 February 2016|publisher=[[Media Wales]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |title=Project Aims to Take Health of the Nation over Next Five Years |newspaper= [[Western Mail (Wales)|Western Mail]] |subscription= yes |via=[[HighBeam Research]] |accessdate= 1 October 2016 |date= 1 March 2016 |url= https://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-444683757.html }}</ref>

